The paper deals with the design of a mechanism for welfare maximization in combinatorial auctions, which is a topic that falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The mechanism is based on a randomized rounding algorithm, which involves optimization over a fractional relaxation of the original problem, and therefore has connections to both discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and convex optimization (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of submodular functions, which are commonly studied in the context of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, these five categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
